# Example clients.local.conf: a single-NAS override for a harness or real
# MikroTik reachable outside Docker's bridge ranges (see clients.conf's
# docker_bridge_dev entry for the common case, which needs no override).
#
# Copy this file to clients.local.conf (an empty clients.local.conf ships
# by default; overwrite it locally) and set TEST_NAS_IP to the harness/NAS's
# real source address. Note this env var must also reach the freeradius
# container: compose.yml's freeradius service does not pass through
# arbitrary host env vars today, so add
# `environment: ["TEST_NAS_IP=${TEST_NAS_IP}"]` to that service (deploy/
# compose.yml, Agent 1's file) the one time this override is needed. Without
# that, skip this file entirely — clients.conf's docker_bridge_dev entry
# already covers every source address Docker's own bridge networks use,
# which is enough for the packet harness and CI.
client test_nas {
	ipaddr = $ENV{TEST_NAS_IP}
	secret = testing123
	require_message_authenticator = no
}
